.TH "pci_epc_add_epf" 9 "pci_epc_add_epf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epc_add_epf \- bind PCI endpoint function to an endpoint controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_epc_add_epf
.BI "(struct pci_epc *epc "  ","
.BI "struct pci_epf *epf "  ","
.BI "enum pci_epc_interface_type type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epc" 12
the EPC device to which the endpoint function should be added
.IP "epf" 12
the endpoint function to be added
.IP "type" 12
Identifies if the EPC is connected to the primary or secondary
interface of EPF
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A PCI endpoint device can have one or more functions. In the case of PCIe,
the specification allows up to 8 PCIe endpoint functions. Invoke
\fBpci_epc_add_epf\fP to add a PCI endpoint function to an endpoint controller.
